    "rationale": "This is a classic and simple example of the Hofmann-Löffler-Freytag reaction. The substrate, N-chloro-N-methylbutan-1-amine, undergoes a 1,5-hydrogen atom transfer via a nitrogen-centered radical to form a carbon-centered radical at the delta-position. Subsequent intramolecular cyclization and workup yield the pyrrolidine product, N-methylpyrrolidine. This example clearly demonstrates the key remote C-H functionalization and cyclization steps characteristic of the reaction family.",
    "collision_avoidance_note": "The reaction involves a simple acyclic N-haloamine substrate and forms a saturated heterocycle. It avoids arenes, complex ring systems, or other highly reactive functional groups that could cause collisions with other named reactions. The core transformation is the remote C-H amination, which is specific to this family and a few related reactions, but the chosen simple substrate minimizes overlap."
  }
